      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: multi-provider API key system with curated model catalogs (v2)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd a multi-provider API key management panel to the dashboard UI, enabling users to configure AI providers and start chatting immediately.\n\nSupersedes #67570 — addresses both review issues:\n- **Branding**: No branding changes. All user-visible text remains \"OpenClaw\".\n- **Masked-key detection**: `getConfiguredProviders()` now accepts masked keys (`***`) from `config.get` snapshots, so providers configured outside this UI session (CLI, page reload) are correctly recognized.\n\n## What's New\n\n### Provider Registry (16 providers)\nOpenAI, Anthropic, Google Gemini, Groq, Mistral, OpenRouter, DeepSeek, Together AI, Fireworks AI, Perplexity, Cohere, xAI, MiniMax, Cerebras, SambaNova, Qwen — each with:\n- Correct `baseUrl` and `api` type matching gateway extensions\n- Curated model catalog with pricing, context windows, and capabilities\n\n### API Key Flow\n1. Click provider → Enter API key → \"Save Key & Add Models\"\n2. `config.patch` writes full provider config: `apiKey + baseUrl + api + models[]`\n3. Models appear instantly from curated catalog (no CORS, no browser-side API calls to providers)\n4. Auto-sets default model + updates current session via `sessions.patch`\n5. Refreshes chat model dropdown (`models.list`) after save\n\n### Model Dropdown Filtering\n- Only shows models from providers that have API keys configured\n- Accepts gateway-masked keys (`***`) so previously configured providers survive page reloads\n\n## Files Changed\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `ui/src/ui/controllers/provider-registry.ts` | **new** — provider metadata + curated model catalogs |\n| `ui/src/ui/controllers/api-key.ts` | **new** — key save, model refresh, session update logic |\n| `ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.ts` | provider list UI, configure panel, model dropdown filter |\n| `ui/src/ui/app-render.ts` | API key button in header bar |\n| `ui/src/ui/app-view-state.ts` | new state fields for API key panel |\n| `ui/src/ui/app.ts` | new `@state()` properties |\n| `ui/src/styles/layout.css` | styling for provider cards, popover, model list |\n\n## Testing\n- Build passes (`vite build` clean, no warnings)\n- Verified: add MiniMax key → 2 models appear → select default → chat responds\n- Verified: page reload preserves configured status (masked key accepted)\n- Verified: no FireClaw/branding changes in diff",
        "branch": "feat/multi-provider-api-key-system-v2",
